query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `jobLocations` (
  `id` int AUTO_INCREMENT NOT NULL,
  `jobId` int NOT NULL,
  `latitude` varchar(50) NOT NULL,
  `longitude` varchar(50) NOT NULL,
  `accuracy` varchar(50),
  `trackingType` enum('en_route','on_site','milestone') NOT NULL,
  `timestamp` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  CONSTRAINT `jobLocations_id` PRIMARY KEY(`id`),
  CONSTRAINT `jobLocations_jobId_fk` FOREIGN KEY (`jobId`) REFERENCES `jobs`(`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  INDEX `jobLocations_jobId_idx` (`jobId`)
)
